mibanswerProfileTable.name: mibanswerProfileTable
mibanswerProfileTable.description: A list of mibanswerProfile profile entries.

mibanswerProfileEntry.name: mibanswerProfileEntry
mibanswerProfileEntry.description: A mibanswerProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibanswerProfile profile.

answerProfile_UseAnswerForAllDefaults.name: answerProfile_UseAnswerForAllDefaults
answerProfile_UseAnswerForAllDefaults.description: When set to Yes, this profile will provide the default values for fields when building profiles. When set to No the factory profile will be used instead.

answerProfile_Force56kbps.name: answerProfile_Force56kbps
answerProfile_Force56kbps.description: If yes then inbound 64 kbps calls are connected at 56 kbps.

answerProfile_ProfilesRequired.name: answerProfile_ProfilesRequired
answerProfile_ProfilesRequired.description: Unused when incoming authentication is used. When authentication is not used a No value in this field indicates that we will create a temporary profile for a user on incoming calls. A Yes value indicates that we must find an existing profile (by matching the caller's IP address). This provided NO security.

answerProfile_ClidAuthMode.name: answerProfile_ClidAuthMode
answerProfile_ClidAuthMode.description: Specifies how calling line identification (CLID) will be used for incoming call authentication.

answerProfile_ClidSelection.name: answerProfile_ClidSelection
answerProfile_ClidSelection.description: Selection of the CLID. An incoming call can optionally specify several CLIDs. A CLID provided by the PSTN (network provided) is considered secure. A CLID provided by the end user (user provided) is secure only if it has been validated by the PSTN (user provided, network verified and passed). Other forms of user CLIDs are considered unsecure.

answerProfile_CallbackClidPrefix.name: answerProfile_CallbackClidPrefix
answerProfile_CallbackClidPrefix.description: Prefix to prepend to the dial number when callback is performed with the CLID number.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_Enabled
answerProfile_PppAnswer_Enabled.description: Set to Yes to enable incoming PPP calls. This includes the PPP variants, MP and MPP.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_ReceiveAuthMode.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_ReceiveAuthMode
answerProfile_PppAnswer_ReceiveAuthMode.description: The type of PPP authentication to use for incoming calls.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_BiDirectionalAut.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_BiDirectionalAuth
answerProfile_PppAnswer_BiDirectionalAut.description: This parameter enables the authentication to be done in both directions. It can be used only with the CHAP, MS-CHAP or CACHE-TOKEN authentication.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_SubstituteSendNa.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_SubstituteSendName
answerProfile_PppAnswer_SubstituteSendNa.description: Name send to the far end, if different from the global system name.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_BridgingGroup.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_BridgingGroup
answerProfile_PppAnswer_BridgingGroup.description: The default bridging group. Interfaces with the same bridging group can bridge to each other. Set to 0 to disable bridging.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_LinkCompression.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_LinkCompression
answerProfile_PppAnswer_LinkCompression.description: The default type of link compression to use for PPP, MP, and MPP calls.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_Mru.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_Mru
answerProfile_PppAnswer_Mru.description: The Maximum Receive Unit, i.e. the largest frame we will accept.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_Lqm.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_Lqm
answerProfile_PppAnswer_Lqm.description: Link Quality Monitoring. Set to Yes to enable the PPP LQM protocol.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_LqmMinimumPeriod.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_LqmMinimumPeriod
answerProfile_PppAnswer_LqmMinimumPeriod.description: The minimum period, in 1/100 of a second, that we will accept/send link quality monitoring packets.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_LqmMaximumPeriod.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_LqmMaximumPeriod
answerProfile_PppAnswer_LqmMaximumPeriod.description: The maximum period, in 1/100 of a second, that we will accept/send link quality monitoring packets.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_CbcpEnabled.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_CbcpEnabled
answerProfile_PppAnswer_CbcpEnabled.description: Enable Microsoft Callback Control Protocol Negotiation.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_IpxHeaderCompres.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_IpxHeaderCompression
answerProfile_PppAnswer_IpxHeaderCompres.description: Use IPX header compression if encapsulation supports it.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_Mtu.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_Mtu
answerProfile_PppAnswer_Mtu.description: The Maximum Transmit Unit, i.e. the largest frame we will send out.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_AuthForAsyncFram.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_AuthForAsyncFramedUsers
answerProfile_PppAnswer_AuthForAsyncFram.description: Determines whether we need to authenticate async framed users.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_MaxPapAuthRetry.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_MaxPapAuthRetry
answerProfile_PppAnswer_MaxPapAuthRetry.description: Number of retries allowed, if PAP authentication fails.

answerProfile_PppAnswer_MaxPppConfigureR.name: answerProfile_PppAnswer_MaxPppConfigureRetry
answerProfile_PppAnswer_MaxPppConfigureR.description: Number of retries allowed, if LCP/NCP fails

answerProfile_MpAnswer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_MpAnswer_Enabled
answerProfile_MpAnswer_Enabled.description: Set to Yes to enable incoming MP calls. This includes the MP variant, MPP.

answerProfile_MpAnswer_MinimumChannels.name: answerProfile_MpAnswer_MinimumChannels
answerProfile_MpAnswer_MinimumChannels.description: The default value for the minimum number of channels in a multi-channel call.

answerProfile_MpAnswer_MaximumChannels.name: answerProfile_MpAnswer_MaximumChannels
answerProfile_MpAnswer_MaximumChannels.description: The default value for the maximum number of channels in a multi-channel call.

answerProfile_MppAnswer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_MppAnswer_Enabled
answerProfile_MppAnswer_Enabled.description: Set to Yes to enable incoming MPP calls.

answerProfile_MppAnswer_DynamicAlgorithm.name: answerProfile_MppAnswer_DynamicAlgorithm
answerProfile_MppAnswer_DynamicAlgorithm.description: The algorithm to use to calculate the average link utilization. Bandwidth changes are performed on the average utilization, not current utilization.

answerProfile_MppAnswer_BandwidthMonitor.name: answerProfile_MppAnswer_BandwidthMonitorDirection
answerProfile_MppAnswer_BandwidthMonitor.description: The direction to monitor link utilization. A unit can monitor transmit, transmit and receive, or turn off monitoring entirely.

answerProfile_MppAnswer_IncrementChannel.name: answerProfile_MppAnswer_IncrementChannelCount
answerProfile_MppAnswer_IncrementChannel.description: Number of channels to increment as a block.

answerProfile_MppAnswer_DecrementChannel.name: answerProfile_MppAnswer_DecrementChannelCount
answerProfile_MppAnswer_DecrementChannel.description: Number of channels to decrement as a block.

answerProfile_MppAnswer_SecondsHistory.name: answerProfile_MppAnswer_SecondsHistory
answerProfile_MppAnswer_SecondsHistory.description: The number of seconds of history that link utilization is averaged over to make bandwidth changes.

answerProfile_MppAnswer_AddPersistence.name: answerProfile_MppAnswer_AddPersistence
answerProfile_MppAnswer_AddPersistence.description: The number of seconds of that the average line utilization must exceed the target utilization before bandwidth will be added.

answerProfile_MppAnswer_SubPersistence.name: answerProfile_MppAnswer_SubPersistence
answerProfile_MppAnswer_SubPersistence.description: The number of seconds of that the average line utilization must fall below the target utilization before bandwidth will be reduced. Bandwidth will not be reduced if the reduced bandwidth would exceed the target utilization.

answerProfile_MppAnswer_TargetUtilizatio.name: answerProfile_MppAnswer_TargetUtilization
answerProfile_MppAnswer_TargetUtilizatio.description: The default value for the target utilization. Bandwidth changes occur when the average utilization exceeds or falls below this value.

answerProfile_FrAnswer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_FrAnswer_Enabled
answerProfile_FrAnswer_Enabled.description: Set to yes to enable incoming FR calls.

answerProfile_TcpClearAnswer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_TcpClearAnswer_Enabled
answerProfile_TcpClearAnswer_Enabled.description: If enabled, incoming calls that match a local profile with a call management type of tcp-raw will automatically be connected via a raw TCP pipe to the host named in the local profile. If disabled, logins that match a tcp-raw profile will be rejected.

answerProfile_AraAnswer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_AraAnswer_Enabled
answerProfile_AraAnswer_Enabled.description: Set to yes to enable incoming ARA calls.

answerProfile_V120Answer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_V120Answer_Enabled
answerProfile_V120Answer_Enabled.description: Set to yes to enable incoming V120 calls.

answerProfile_V120Answer_FrameLength.name: answerProfile_V120Answer_FrameLength
answerProfile_V120Answer_FrameLength.description: The default frame length to use for incoming V.120 connections.

answerProfile_X25Answer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_X25Answer_Enabled
answerProfile_X25Answer_Enabled.description: If enabled, incoming calls that match a local profile with a call management type of x25 will be accepted.

answerProfile_X25Answer_X25Profile.name: answerProfile_X25Answer_X25Profile
answerProfile_X25Answer_X25Profile.description: Name of the x25 profile that this profile is associated with.

answerProfile_X25Answer_AutoCallX121Addr.name: answerProfile_X25Answer_AutoCallX121Address
answerProfile_X25Answer_AutoCallX121Addr.description: X.121 address to auto-call upon session startup.

answerProfile_X25Answer_X3CustomProf.name: answerProfile_X25Answer_X3CustomProf
answerProfile_X25Answer_X3CustomProf.description: Custom profile enter a string for a custom X.3 profile if x3Prof says custom.

answerProfile_EuAnswer_DceAddr.name: answerProfile_EuAnswer_DceAddr
answerProfile_EuAnswer_DceAddr.description: The address of the DCE side of the link when the EUNET UI protocol is used.

answerProfile_EuAnswer_DteAddr.name: answerProfile_EuAnswer_DteAddr
answerProfile_EuAnswer_DteAddr.description: The address of the DTE side of the link when the EUNET UI protocol is used.

answerProfile_EuAnswer_Mru.name: answerProfile_EuAnswer_Mru
answerProfile_EuAnswer_Mru.description: The Maximum Receive Unit, i.e. the largest frame we will accept when the EUNET UI protocol is used.

answerProfile_IpAnswer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_IpAnswer_Enabled
answerProfile_IpAnswer_Enabled.description: Set to yes to enable IP routing on incoming calls using encapsulation protocols that support IP routing.

answerProfile_IpAnswer_VjHeaderPredictio.name: answerProfile_IpAnswer_VjHeaderPrediction
answerProfile_IpAnswer_VjHeaderPredictio.description: Set to yes to enable Van Jacobson IP header prediction to be negotiated on incoming calls using encapsulation protocols that support this feature.

answerProfile_IpAnswer_AssignAddress.name: answerProfile_IpAnswer_AssignAddress
answerProfile_IpAnswer_AssignAddress.description: Set to yes if this unit is configured with one or more pools of IP addresses that will be used as a source of addresses to assign to incoming callers.

answerProfile_IpAnswer_RoutingMetric.name: answerProfile_IpAnswer_RoutingMetric
answerProfile_IpAnswer_RoutingMetric.description: The default metric assigned to routes created for incoming calls.

answerProfile_IpAnswer_PrivateRouteProfi.name: answerProfile_IpAnswer_PrivateRouteProfileRequired
answerProfile_IpAnswer_PrivateRouteProfi.description: Parameter to decide default action,if private route table not found. If set to yes, the call will be cleared if the private route profile cannot be found. If set to no, the call will be allowed to complete, even if the private route profile cannot be found.

answerProfile_IpAnswer_PoolForAsyncFrame.name: answerProfile_IpAnswer_PoolForAsyncFramedUser
answerProfile_IpAnswer_PoolForAsyncFrame.description: Pool number to be used for dial-in asynchronous PPP framed users with out authentication.

answerProfile_IpxAnswer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_IpxAnswer_Enabled
answerProfile_IpxAnswer_Enabled.description: Set to Yes to enable incoming IPX calls.

answerProfile_IpxAnswer_PeerMode.name: answerProfile_IpxAnswer_PeerMode
answerProfile_IpxAnswer_PeerMode.description: Enable/disable full routing between peer or use the pool to assign a network number.

answerProfile_SessionInfo_CallFilter.name: answerProfile_SessionInfo_CallFilter
answerProfile_SessionInfo_CallFilter.description: The name of the filter used to determine if a packet should cause the idle timer to be reset or, when the answer profile is used for connection profile defaults, if a call should be placed.

answerProfile_SessionInfo_DataFilter.name: answerProfile_SessionInfo_DataFilter
answerProfile_SessionInfo_DataFilter.description: The name of the filter used to determine if packets should be forwarded or dropped.

answerProfile_SessionInfo_FilterPersiste.name: answerProfile_SessionInfo_FilterPersistence
answerProfile_SessionInfo_FilterPersiste.description: Determines if filters should persist between calls.

answerProfile_SessionInfo_FilterRequired.name: answerProfile_SessionInfo_FilterRequired
answerProfile_SessionInfo_FilterRequired.description: If No, the call will be allowed to come up even if the specified filter was not found either locally, in the cache or in RADIUS. If Yes, then the call will be cleared if the specified filter was not found either locally, in the cache or in RADIUS.

answerProfile_SessionInfo_IdleTimer.name: answerProfile_SessionInfo_IdleTimer
answerProfile_SessionInfo_IdleTimer.description: The number of seconds of no activity before a call will be dropped. The value 0 disables the idle timer.

answerProfile_SessionInfo_TsIdleMode.name: answerProfile_SessionInfo_TsIdleMode
answerProfile_SessionInfo_TsIdleMode.description: The method used to determine when the terminal server idle session timer is reset.

answerProfile_SessionInfo_TsIdleTimer.name: answerProfile_SessionInfo_TsIdleTimer
answerProfile_SessionInfo_TsIdleTimer.description: The number of seconds of no activity as defined by the idle mode before a session will be terminated.

answerProfile_SessionInfo_MaxCallDuratio.name: answerProfile_SessionInfo_MaxCallDuration
answerProfile_SessionInfo_MaxCallDuratio.description: The number of minutes of connect time before a call will be dropped. The value 0 disables the connection timer.

answerProfile_X75Answer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_X75Answer_Enabled
answerProfile_X75Answer_Enabled.description: Set to yes to enable incoming X75 calls.

answerProfile_X75Answer_KFramesOutstandi.name: answerProfile_X75Answer_KFramesOutstanding
answerProfile_X75Answer_KFramesOutstandi.description: Number of frames outstanding before we require an ack. Defaults to 7.

answerProfile_X75Answer_N2Retransmission.name: answerProfile_X75Answer_N2Retransmissions
answerProfile_X75Answer_N2Retransmission.description: Number of retransmissions allowed. Defaults to 10.

answerProfile_X75Answer_T1RetranTimer.name: answerProfile_X75Answer_T1RetranTimer
answerProfile_X75Answer_T1RetranTimer.description: Number of milliseconds between retransmissions. Defaults to 1000.

answerProfile_X75Answer_FrameLength.name: answerProfile_X75Answer_FrameLength
answerProfile_X75Answer_FrameLength.description: Frame length to use for incoming X.75 connections. Defaults to 1024.

answerProfile_FramedOnly.name: answerProfile_FramedOnly
answerProfile_FramedOnly.description: A profile can be restricted to only doing the framed commands (ppp, mpp, slip, and quit) by setting this to YES

answerProfile_HdlcNrmAnswer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_HdlcNrmAnswer_Enabled
answerProfile_HdlcNrmAnswer_Enabled.description: Set to yes to enable incoming HDLC-NRM calls.

answerProfile_Visa2Answer_Enabled.name: answerProfile_Visa2Answer_Enabled
answerProfile_Visa2Answer_Enabled.description: Set to yes to enable incoming VISA2 calls.

answerProfile_AtmAnswer_SvcEnabled.name: answerProfile_AtmAnswer_SvcEnabled
answerProfile_AtmAnswer_SvcEnabled.description: Set to yes to enable ATM SVC athentication on incoming calls.

answerProfile_PriorityAnswer_PacketClass.name: answerProfile_PriorityAnswer_PacketClassification
answerProfile_PriorityAnswer_PacketClass.description: Method used to classify PPP packets.

answerProfile_PriorityAnswer_MaxRtpPacke.name: answerProfile_PriorityAnswer_MaxRtpPacketDelay
answerProfile_PriorityAnswer_MaxRtpPacke.description: Maximum delay for RTP packets in milli-seconds. Used for calculating the fragment size for the non-rtp traffic using the same link.

answerProfile_PriorityAnswer_NoHighPrioP.name: answerProfile_PriorityAnswer_NoHighPrioPktDuration
answerProfile_PriorityAnswer_NoHighPrioP.description: The number of seconds of no high priority packets before disabling IP fragmentation of low priority packets. The value 0 disables checking duration of no high priority packet.
